                            <comment id="13133880" author="pqueixalos" created="Mon, 24 Oct 2011 07:58:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Concerning the HSLFExtractor, this is already fixed in trunk. getAuthor() is checked before calling xhtml.characters( comment.getAuthor() );&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13133898" author="tkrah" created="Mon, 24 Oct 2011 08:45:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, but there are more calls to this method which are not checked too, not only the author call. So imho the best option here is to be defensive and check and make a NoOp and log a warning or error, at least it should not fail here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
